What is the output of this code?

int[] arr = {5, 3, 8, 1, 9, 2};
Arrays.sort(arr);
System.out.println(arr[0] + " " + arr[arr.length-1]);

What is the time complexity of this code?

for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
  for (int j = i; j < n; j++) {
    System.out.println(i + j);
  }
}

What is the time complexity of this code?

for (int i = 1; i < n; i = i * 2) {
  System.out.println(i);
}
